Better coordination would help fix various [market failures](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Market_failure).

# Mechanisms

- [Dominant assurance contracts](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Assurance_contract#Dominant_assurance_contracts)
- [Direct democracy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Direct_democracy)


# Platforms

**Relevant features:**

- Ability to enforce commitments
- Ability to filter who counts as a person who can join a campaign


**Existing platforms:**

- [Actuator](http://actuator.herokuapp.com/)
- [Collaction](https://collaction.org/): Unlock based on the number of participants
- [Cryptounlocked](https://cryptounlocked.wetrust.io/): Unlock based on the amount of money raised
- [Free State Project](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_State_Project): US-Americans sharing the libertarian political view coordinating to move to the same state, so together they can have a greater impact on local politics
- [Indiegogo](http://indiegogo.com/)
- [KickStarter](http://www.kickstarter.com/)

**Discontinued platforms:**

- [PledgeBank](http://www.pledgebank.com/)
- [Thunderclap](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thunderclap_(website)): to share a Facebook post at the same time
- [We the People](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/We_the_People_(petitioning_system)): letter sent to the White House after a number of petitions are made

